  "texts": [
    "Although prompt-tuning plays an important role in off-the-shelf performance, it is unlikely that it would affect our results given the extent to which we fine-tuned the GLMs.Although most GLMs are initially trained in an unsupervised way on large corpora of text data (Radford et al., 2019), our addition of human-annotated labels puts the automated scoring task in the realm of supervised learning.",
    "During evaluation of model performance on the test set, human-annotated scores were omitted, and model-generated scores were extracted as output.",
    "Parameter-efficient fine-tuningModels were loaded through Huggingface-hub, quantized into smaller, 4-bit models using bitsandbytes, and trained using low-rank adaptors (LoRA).",
    "Learning rate was set to 2 × 10 -4 (except for Gemma-1.1, which was set to 1 × 10 -4 to ensure convergence), with a linear rate decay over 10 epochs.",
    "r and α, key parameters for LoRA, were each set to 32."
  ],
